  <description type="morphology">Stolons usually densely spreading-hairy. Leaves: petiole usually densely spreading-hairy; leaflet blade usually bluish green, slightly glaucous, sometimes dull, terminal leaflets ovate-obovate to cuneate or truncate, sometimes slightly leathery, margins serrate or crenate only in distal 1/3, teeth: relative number 0.1–0.4. Peduncles and pedicels densely spreading-hairy. Flowers 15–18.6 mm diam. (pistillate), 16.3–26 mm diam. (bisexual and staminate). Fruits: bractlets clasping or slightly spreading. 2n = 56.</description>
